column137: Throughout this study, I have largely left this blank, but for this final survey I would like to clarify some things and provide extra insight.  For a long time now I have struggled with depression, anxiety, and burnout.  I struggle with inactivity and beat myself up constantly. Games provide not only an escape from the real world for me, they can provide an escape from my own negative self talk and allow me to act without over thinking.  They give me structure and purpose that I can't seem to provide for myself in life.  I do use this as a crutch too often and at times play games when I'm not even in the mood just to distract me from the general discomfort I face simply from existing.

column137:
Just that I had to struggle through the Black Throne section of Darksiders & that's why I've been answering so negatively in this survey. The rest of the game was pretty good, as is the parts after, but the puzzles & void walker ability are just so fucking aggravating. I really wanted to finish the game, though, so I had to do some struggling. ha. Took, like, 5 hours because every time I'd stop for the night, it would toss me back to the beginning of the stage/level/land. Such a bad mechanic!

Plus, I finally gave in & watched a walkthrough & the absolute dipshit who recorded those videos would both: not shut up & did a pretty poor job of explaining what they were doing for the puzzles. ugh. Kuddlesnot has got to be one of the worst "let's play" people who I've had the misfortune of watching. Man, makes me want to record my own walkthrough because there's no way I'd make a worse one! haha. So, that's been the issue this week. I'm hoping that Darksiders II manages the puzzles a bit better, if I give that a go before BotW TotK comes out. Really looking forward to it.

column137: I had a week off work and spent almost all of it organising my house and writing code for fun. I sometimes get into moods where I do these two things almost compulsively, and they're really productive so I just roll with them, in practically all my waking hours for days at a time. This has left very little time for gaming - I have played no single player games at all, and what I have played has been mostly for social purposes. I felt really great about what I got done in my week off and didn't feel lonely or isolated or anything like that, but I do feel like I need to reconnect with my xbox friends now having gone from hanging out with them for hours every single night to barely speaking to them for a fortnight. We have kept up sporadically on Discord, but it's not the same as hanging out in a voice chat.
